	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Makes sense to me. The menu can trampoline to the game's reset code when you select it, leaving the actual reset vector to point to a bootstrap that can initialize the mapper to start the menu after a reset.<br /><br />In addition, you'd be able to exit to the multicart menu by indirectly jumping through the reset vector. There you go, an &quot;exit game&quot; option at your title screen. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


